        "section_value": "The patient reports a long-standing history of high blood pressure, taking chlorthalidone intermittently due to stomach upset. He experiences throbbing headaches, often located on the top of his head, which are sometimes accompanied by dizziness and blurry vision. He admits to taking Tylenol for the headaches, which provides some relief. He also reports occasional nausea. He has been eating a lot of McDonald's, including large fries, and admits to eating a lot of his kids' Easter candy over the weekend, which may have contributed to his elevated blood sugar levels. He reports forgetting to take his medications frequently.",
