        "heading": "O",
        "section_value": "Blood pressure was recorded at 172/98 mmHg this morning. The patient's heart rate is 78 bpm and regular. Oxygen saturation is 98% on room air. A one plus pitting edema is noted bilaterally on the lower extremities. A two out of six systolic ejection murmur is auscultated. Lung sounds are clear bilaterally. The patient's skin is warm and dry. Neurological exam is unremarkable.",
